AIM: 
To write a C program to evaluate the expression πr² (area of a circle). 


ALGORITHM: 
1. Start the program. 
2. Declare variables for radius and area (float type). 
3. Read the radius value from the user. 
4. Use the formula: 
5. area=π×r×r 
6. Display the calculated area. 
7. Stop the program.

PROGRAM: 
#include <stdio.h> 
#define PI 3.1416 
int main() { 
float radius, area; 
printf("Enter radius: "); 
scanf("%f", &radius); 
area = PI * radius * radius; 
printf("Area of the circle = %.2f\n", area); 
return 0; 
} 
 

SAMPLE OTPUT: 
Enter radius: 7 
Area of the circle = 153.94
